caption: Table 1: Comparison of algorithms for robust bandits and dueling bandits.
description: The table compares different algorithms for robust bandits and dueling bandits, showing their settings (e.g., K-armed bandits, linear bandits, contextual bandits) and the regret bounds they achieve.  The algorithms are categorized into bandits and dueling bandits, and the regret bounds reflect their performance under different settings and levels of adversarial corruption or uncertainty.  The table highlights the differences in algorithm design and their resulting theoretical guarantees.
